values:
I love today! 
I found out today from my results slip that I'm 10th in my class, which has 40 people. I'm also 44th in my level, which has 198 people. I love today!! 
I also found lots of very cool and hilarious The Fray videos which I spent about an hour obsessing over just now! Ha ha ha. I always love it when I find cool videos that I've never seen before. Who doesn't, huh? 
They were at Madrid in Spain for a concert, and during a break Isaac began speaking spanish! Unbelievable, but he sounds really good at it! His voice is always beautiful anyway! His spanish ain't good, though, ha ha ha! And that's what's so funny! 

Isaac was like: (ALL&nbsp;IN&nbsp;SPANISH&nbsp;UNLESS&nbsp;SAID) 
&quot;Okay, so how are you all doin' today?&quot; 
(in english) &quot;Sorry, my spanish isn't very good...&quot; 
(spots a group of girls with the letters of &quot;The Fray&quot; painted on their palms) 
&quot;There's... three girls with our names on their hands...&quot; 
&quot;Hold on, I gotta get a picture of this...&quot; 
(Rod runs up on stage and takes the picture (!!!), audience cheers) 
&quot;Okay now... this is really important so listen a moment...&quot; 
&quot;I've got a joke here... and it's kind of bad... but listen..&quot; 
&quot;My friends here don't know how to speak spanish so I want to impress them a little...&quot; 
&quot;So you guys better laugh!&quot; 
(audience roars with laughter!!!) 
&quot;Wait a minute, I haven't started the joke yet! Shut up!&quot; 
(here I didn't know what he said...) 
(They start to sing they're cover of shakira's &quot;hips don't lie&quot;, so I guess Isaac must have been saying that it was next.) 

This might sound confusing, but someone commented on the video, someone from Spain, no doubt, that there's this history of some guy insulting some Spanish king by asking him to shut up. Ha ha ha ha ha. Isaac cracks me up. I was laughing throughout the whole thing. 


So, now I'm deciding what movie to watch with Shirley on monday. Which would be better? My sister's keeper? Or love happens? &quot;Love happens&quot; is that Jennifer Aniston movie. It seems kind of nice. My sister's keeper might be too sad, and I might not really want too sad movies. I feel like watching &quot;Julie and Julia&quot; but it's released a few weeks ago so the showtimes are all really late, like 6pm+. So, I don't think we can watch it... Awwwww. I wanna see french food! And of course the movie sounds nice. I shall tell Shirley about them in school tomorrow and ask her which she prefers. &quot;Love happens&quot; is the only romance movie showing, so I'd probably want that, compared to a really saddening movie... 

Well, dinner is gonna be ready soon. I'm feelin' extremely bored. 
I seriously hope to be able to take Literature next year, and also to go to class 3-4! I must! Or I'll feel so angry. 
Alrighty, I'm off.
